eat\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|13}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| Title           = Last Night in Paradise\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|13}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n{{Episode table/part|p=Week 2|c=#A7BCE2|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| Title           = Moving in Together\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|20}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| Title           = Meet the Parents\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|20}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| Title           = Countdown to I Do's\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|20}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 9\n| Title           = Bachelor & Bachelorette Parties\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|20}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n{{Episode table/part|p=Week 3|c=#A7BCE2|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| Title           = The Weddings\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|27}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n{{Episode table/part|p=Special|c=#A7BCE2|nopart=y}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 11\n| Title           = Reunion\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|5}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = A7BCE2\n}}\n}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Filming ===\nFilming took place in [[Atlanta|Atlanta, Georgia]], from October 9, 2018, and lasted 38 days up until the weddings. The couples met face-to-face on October 19.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brockington |first1=Ariana |title=The First Season Of Love Is Blind Was Filmed A Long, Long Time Ago |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2020/02/9440895/when-was-love-is-blind-filmed-netflix-dating-show |website=Refinery29 |accessdate=February 22, 2020 |date=February 20, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The ten days in the pods were shot at [[Pinewood Atlanta Studios]] in [[Fayetteville, Georgia|Fayetteville]].<ref name=\"pods location\">{{cite web |last1=Patel |first1=Varun |title=Where is the Love is Blind Set Located? |url=https://www.thecinemaholic.com/where-is-the-love-is-blind-set-located/ |website=TheCinemaholic |accessdate=February 14, 2020|date=February 12, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Then, after the newly engaged couples left the pods, filming took place at the Grand Velas Riviera Maya in [[Playa del Carmen]], [[Mexico]], when all the couples went on a retreat. The relationships that made it through the retreat in Mexico move in together in an apartment complex.<ref name=\"mashable review\">{{cite web |last1=Crimmins |first1=Tricia |title='Love Is Blind' is the bizarre reality TV experiment you've been craving |url=https://mashable.com/article/love-is-blind-review/ |website=Mashable |accessdate=February 14, 2020 |date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> After the retreat, the couples headed back to Atlanta to the Spectrum on Spring apartment building, where they spent the rest of the time filming up until the weddings.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Koerner |first1=Allyson |title=Where Was 'Love Is Blind' Filmed? The Pods Weren't Too Far From Home |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/where-was-love-is-blind-filmed-the-pods-werent-too-far-from-home-21815887 |website=Bustle |accessdate=February 22, 2020 |language=English |date=February 20, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"wedding day\">{{cite web |last1=Brockington |first1=Ariana |title=Love Is Blind Makes The Most Of Its Filming Locations |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2020/02/9391829/where-is-love-is-blind-filmed-locations-atlanta-netflix |website=Refinery29 |accessdate=February 22, 2020 |language=English |date=February 20, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The weddings took place at two event spaces called Flourish Atlanta<ref name=\"wedding day\"/> and The Estate<ref>{{cite web |last1=White |first1=Brett |title='Love Is Blind' on Netflix: You Can Get Married at the Same Place as the Couples |url=https://decider.com/2020/02/27/love-is-blind-finale-wedding-venue-netflix/ |website=decider.com |publisher=Decider |accessdate=February 29, 2020 |language=English |date=February 27, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> on November 15.\n\n=== Release ===\nThe trailer for ''Love Is Blind'' was released on January 30, 2020.<ref name=\"trailer\">{{cite web |author1=Netflix |title=Love is Blind - Official Trailer - Netflix |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s2eBAFt3L_0 |website=YouTube |accessdate=1 February 2020 |language=English |date=30 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> With the trailer, it was announced that the ten-episode series would be released on a three-week schedule: the first five episodes were released on February 13, 2020, the next four on February 20, and the finale on February 27.<ref name=\"entertainment weekly\"/>\n\nOn February 26, 2020, Netflix announced a reunion special available on [[YouTube]] on March 5.<ref name=\"reunion\"/>\n\n=== Unaired engagements ===\nA total of eight couples got engaged among the participants. In addition to the six couples shown on the series, couples Westley Baer and Lexie Skipper and Rory Newbrough and Danielle Drouin also got engaged in the show. Newbrough told ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'', \"As we were preparing to go to the Mexico trip, the leads of the show came in and said, 'Hey, we were expecting maybe one or two [engagements]. The shows we've done before, we've never had this much success. We prepared for five. Then we got eight engagements, so we had to pick who we were going to follow.' We got our phones back. They thanked us graciously and said, 'Sorry, we just don\u2019t have enough to cover everybody.'\"<ref name=\"failed engagements\"/>\n\nAfter getting engaged in the pods, Baer and Skipper continued to date for three months before breaking up. Newbrough and Drouin took a week-long trip to Miami together after getting engaged. They broke up after returning from the trip and Drouin decided to pursue a relationship with another participant on the show, Matt Thomas. Thomas and Drouin later split as well.<ref name=\"failed engagements\"/>\n\n== Reception ==\nOn February 28, the day after the finale aired, ''Love Is Blind'' became Netflix's number-one trending program<ref>{{cite web |last1=Abad-Santos |first1=Alex |title=Who got married in Love Is Blind's volatile season finale? |url=https://www.vox.com/2020/2/29/21157983/love-is-blind-reunion-spoilers-marriages-breakups |website=vox.com |publisher=Vox |accessdate=February 29, 2020 |language=English |date=February 29, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> coming just days after Netflix introduced its new trending top ten list on their website on February 24.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=Cameron |title=Now - for the first time - you can see what's popular on Netflix |url=https://media.netflix.com/en/company-blog/see-whats-popular-on-netflix |website=media.netflix.com |publisher=Netflix Media Center |accessdate=February 29, 2020 |language=English |date=February 24, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTricia Crimmins of ''[[Mashable]]'' reviewed the first five episodes of ''Love Is Blind'' following their initial release on February 13. Comparing it to ''[[The Bachelor (American TV series)|The Bachelor]]'', Crimmins called the series \"the bizarre reality TV experiment you've been craving\". She comments that you never know what the couples will do next, even down to the altar at the wedding, making the series \"harmless, entertaining, and satisfying.\"<ref name=\"mashable review\"/>\n\nLucy Mangan of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave ''Love Is Blind'' a rating of 2 out of 5 stars, calling it toxic, revolting, but extremely addictive. She says that ''Love Is Blind'' is the final nail in the coffin of humanity; however, in terms of reality television, she states that it is good because it \"exploits emotional frailties, profaning the sacred, making the private and precious public and worthless and turning it into voyeuristic ratings-bait.\" Despite all of this, she recommends the show as a casual reality television binge, similar to ''[[The Bachelor (American TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mangan |first1=Lucy |title=Love Is Blind review: toxic, revolting \u2013 and totally addictive |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2020/feb/13/love-is-blind-review-toxic-revolting-and-totally-addictive |website=theguardian.com |publisher=The Guardian |accessdate=February 29, 2020 |language=English |date=February 13, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nKristen Baldwin of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called the series \"intensely tragic yet riveting.\" She criticized the series, saying that the first four episodes in the pods feel new and fresh, but once the engaged couples enter the real world, it feels like just another bad dating reality television show. Baldwin also called it depressing, citing the contestants always saying, \"If I don't get married now, I never will.\" Overall, Baldwin gave ''Love Is Blind'' a [[Grading systems by country#United States|C+ rating]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Baldwin |first1=Kristen |title=I watched all of Netflix's Love Is Blind and I hate myself: Review |url=https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2020/02/10/love-is-blind-netflix-review/ |website=ew.com |publisher=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=February 29, 2020 |language=English |date=February 10, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, 2020, ''Love Is Blind'' was renewed for a second and third season.<ref name=\"season 2 renewal\"/><ref name=\"renewal\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Netflix original current series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Love Is Blind}}\n[[Category:2020 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:American dating and relationship reality television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Netflix original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series about marriage]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed at Pinewood Atlanta Studios]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Atlanta]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Wedding television shows]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|2020 Netflix reality series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Love Is Blind\n| image                    = Love is Blind title card.png\n| caption                  = Title card for the series.\n| genre                    = [[Reality television|Reality]]\n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Nick Lachey]]\n* [[Vanessa Lachey]]\n}}\n| narrated                 = \n| country                  = [[United States]]\n| theme_music_composer     = \n| opentheme                = \n| language                 = English\n| num_series               = 1\n| num_episodes             = 11\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Chris Coelen\n* Sam Dean\n* Ally Simpson\n* Eric Detwiler\n}}\n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 48\u201384 minutes\n| channel                  = [[Netflix]]\n| company                  = [[ProSiebenSat.1 Media#Red Arrow Studios|Kinetic Content]]\n| distributor              = \n| picture_format           = 16:9\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|2|13}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}}\n| website                  = \n}}\n\n'''''Love Is Blind''''' is a [[Dating show|dating]] [[reality television]] series, produced by [[ProSiebenSat.1 Media#Red Arrow Studios|Kinetic Content]]<ref name=\"new york post\">{{cite web |last1=Hegedus |first1=Eric |title=Netflix's 'Love Is Blind' confirms reality TV dating is pure trash |url=https://nypost.com/2020/01/30/netflixs-love-is-blind-confirms-reality-tv-dating-is-pure-trash/ |website=New York Post |accessdate=February 1, 2020|date=January 30, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> and created by Chris Coelen<ref name=\"other engagements\">{{cite web |last1=Kinane |first1=Ruth |title=Love Is Blind creator on what they didn't show \u2014 including even more proposals |url=https://ew.com/tv/2020/02/14/love-is-blind-netflix-dating-show-creator-what-you-didnt-see/ |website=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=February 16, 2020 |date=February 14, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> which premiered on [[Netflix]] on February 13, 2020 as part of a three-week event.<ref name=\"entertainment weekly\">{{cite web |last1=Snierson |first1=Dan |title=Watch singles get engaged without meeting in person in trailer for Netflix reality series |url=https://ew.com/tv/2020/01/30/love-is-blind-netflix-trailer/ |website=Entertainment Weekly |accessdate=February 1, 2020|date=January 30, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>  The series has been compared to ''[[Married at First Sight (American TV series)|Married at First Sight]]'', which was also produced by Kinetic Content,<ref name=\"new york post\"/> and ''[[The Bachelor (American TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.<ref name=\"gq\">{{cite web |last1=Grebey |first1=James |title=Netflix's Love Is Blind Is the Dystopian Dating Reality Show We Deserve |url=https://www.gq.com/story/netflix-love-is-blind-dating-show |website=GQ |accessdate=February 1, 2020|date=January 30, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> There were a total of ten episodes released in addition to a reunion special that was released on Netflix and [[YouTube]] on March 5.<ref name=\"reunion\">{{cite web |last1=Heldman |first1=Breanne |title=Netflix Announces Love Is Blind Cast Reunion to Reveal Which Couples Have Stayed Together |url=https://people.com/tv/netflix-announces-love-is-blind-cast-reunion-to-reveal-which-couples-have-stayed-together/ |website=people.com |publisher=People |accessdate=February 29, 2020 |language=English |date=February 26, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Netflix]] renewed ''Love Is Blind'' for a second and third season on March 24, 2020.<ref name=\"season 2 renewal\">{{cite web |author1=Netflix |title=Moments of Joy from Real Netflix Shows - New season announcements |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u83uo2_qWo0 |website=youtube.com |publisher=YouTube |accessdate=March 24, 2020 |language=English |date=March 24, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"renewal\">{{cite web |last1=Thorne |first1=Will |title=Netflix Orders More 'Love Is Blind,' 'The Circle,' 'Rhythm + Flow' and Marie Kondo |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/love-is-blind-the-circle-rhythm-flow-marie-kondo-renewed-netflix-1203543386/ |website=variety.com |publisher=Variety |accessdate=March 24, 2020 |language=English |date=March 24, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Format ==\nThe series follows thirty men and women hoping to find love. For ten days in a [[speed dating]] format, the men and women date each other in different \"pods\" where they can talk to each other, but not see each other. Whenever they decided, the men were able to propose to the woman they want to get married to. After the proposal, and meeting face-to-face for the first time, the engaged couples headed to a couples retreat in [[Playa del Carmen]], [[Mexico]]. During this trip they spent time getting to know their partners, and were able to meet the other couples participating in the experiment. \n\nFollowing the couples retreat, the engaged couples moved to the same apartment complex back in Atlanta. While at the apartments, they all met their partners' families and explored their partners' living conditions. At the altar on the day of the wedding, the engaged couples carried out wedding ceremonies and needed to make their final decisions at the altar about whether to split up or get married, answering the question \"Is love blind?\"\n\n==Season summary==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1%;\" | Season\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10%;\" | Original Run\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"20%\" | Couples\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"5%\" | Proposal\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"5%\" | Still together\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"34%\" | Relationship notes\n|-\n|  rowspan=\"6\"| 1\n| rowspan=\"6\"| February 13, 2020 - March 5, 2020\n| Lauren Speed & Cameron Hamilton\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| The two got married in November 2018, during the filming of the 1st season of Love is Blind. The couple are still together as of {{currentmonthname}} {{currentyear}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/love-is-blind-lauren-cameron-still-together/|title=Love is Blind's Lauren Speed and Cameron Hamilton Are Still Married!|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|last=Heldman|first=Breanne|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> \n|-\n| Amber Pike & Matthew Barnett\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| The two got married in November 2018, during the filming of the 1st season of Love is Blind. The couple are still together as of {{currentmonthname}} {{currentyear}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/amber-barnett-are-still-together-after-love-is-blind-theyve-been-busy-22058861|title=Love is Blind's Amber and Barnett Are Still Together!|work=[[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]]|last=Blanton|first=Kayla|date=March 2, 2020|accessdate=March 6, 2020}}</ref> \n|-\n| Gianinna Gibelli & Damian Powers\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| Although the couple got engaged during the show, they spilt on their wedding day. It was revealed at the reunion special that the two were back together. The couple are still together as of {{currentmonthname}} {{currentyear}}.  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/uk/entertainment/a31235244/love-is-blind-damian-giannina-back-together/|title=Love is Blind's Damian and Giannina Are Back Together|work=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|last=Shenton|first=Zoe|date=March 5, 2020|accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n|